5|$|Abbott asked Donen {{to appear}} in the chorus of his next Broadway show Best Foot Forward. He quickly became the show's {{assistant}} stage manager, and Kelly asked him to be his assistant choreographer. Eventually Donen was fired from Best Foot Forward, but in 1942 was <b>the</b> <b>stage</b> <b>manager</b> and assistant choreographer for Abbott's next show Beat the Band. In 1946, Donen briefly returned to Broadway to help choreograph dance numbers for Call Me Mister.|$|E
25|$|The play {{is set in}} {{the actual}} theatre where the play is being performed, but the year is always 1938. <b>The</b> <b>Stage</b> <b>Manager</b> of the 1938 {{production}} introduces the play-within-the-play which {{is set in the}} fictional community of Grover's Corners, New Hampshire. <b>The</b> <b>Stage</b> <b>Manager</b> gives the coordinates of Grover's Corners as 42°40′ north latitude and 70°37′ west longitude (those coordinates are actually in Massachusetts, about a thousand feet off the coast of Rockport).|$|E
