5000|$|A {{number of}} key scenes {{required}} the audience to both see the play-within-the-play {{and at the same}} time observe the realism of <b>the</b> <b>stage</b> <b>manager's</b> operations in <b>the</b> wings. To achieve this result and to make both elements simultaneous, the major part of the production had to hang on specially-constructed overhead steel tracks. Synchronized electric motors slowly moved <b>the</b> <b>stage</b> pictures off into the wings far enough to expose <b>the</b> <b>stage</b> <b>manager's</b> desk and actors and stagehands offstage awaiting their cues.|$|R
